an automatic grading scheme for simple programming exercises.wa discussion is given of alterations that weremade to a typical university operating system to record the results of programming exercises in threedifferent languages, including assembly language.  in this computer-controlled grading scheme provisionis made for testing with programmer-supplied data and for final runs with system-supplied data.  exercisesrun under the scheme may be mixed with other programs, and no special recognition of exercises by the operators is necessary.cacm may, hext, j. b.winings, j. w..kautomatic grading program, programming exercises.c. . .ca jb february ,   : pm